article.headline: Army 54, New Hampshire 46
article.story: WEST POINT, N.Y. -- Josh Miller scored 13 points and Army beat New Hampshire 54-46 in a cold-shooting game for both teams on Tuesday afternoon. Cleveland Richard and Jeremy Hence each had 11 points for the Black Knights (9-2), who shot 39.2 percent (20-for-51) from the floor. Army?s nine wins in its first 11 games marks the program's best start since the 2006-07 squad also started 9-2. The Wildcats (4-5) shot even worse from the field, hitting 31.1 percent (14-for-45). Tyrone Conley led New Hampshire with a game-high 17 points. Alvin Abreu finished with 12 points and Dane DiLiegro had 15 rebounds. Army went into halftime with a 24-18 lead. The Black Knights, who won their fourth in a row, increased their lead to open the second half by outscoring New Hampshire 17-5 to take a 41-23 lead -- their largest of the game -- on Miller's 3 with 13:10 left.
